{
  "stem": "21354.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I was a friendly alien.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were enemy aliens.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All to-- all had to leave.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The British police didn't distinguish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You were an alien, an alien.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We came to London.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I came to London, found myself a job.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And with a job, I found myself lodgings, also with a Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From then onwards, it became increasingly difficult, increasingly difficult.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And letters did pass, or postcards, but with very little.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But towards the end of '39, that stopped.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Had no further communication.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In '39.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it's a strange feeling.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For me, Britain was my country.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If they didn't adopt me, I adopted Britain.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when I later on joined the Air Force, I destroyed everything that I had-- all my letters, everything.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I have hardly any photographs left.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, stupidity.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Or a sense of pride, that I had been given the opportunity to join the elite, the Royal Air Force, and certainly no one-- I didn't want anybody ever to know that I came from Germany or had any contact with the enemy.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Basically, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know-- I didn't know anything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We knew about concentration camps, we knew about-- because soon after, my father was taken to Buchenwald, which was a notorious concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But all that was not known to me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was known to me-- it was known to me later on, as we moved from-- that was really much later, in 1944, I was with the Tactical Air Force.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we moved from the first day, from D-Day onwards, from France, Belgium, Holland, as we moved up, we learned there were concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know what was happening until after the war when we learned about Belsen.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 87,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1940, we did-- I didn't know anything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 88,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
